# Domain Core — Smart Prosthetics ERP

Source: `docs/new_analysis_by_client.md`

## System purpose

ERP for a prosthetics manufacturing center: EMR, contract entities, inventory (WAC + barcode), event-driven workflow, background pricing, BI dashboards, immutable audit log.

## Non-negotiable separation

- **Civilian (`Patient::TYPE_CIVILIAN`)**: full financial path — quote → contract approval → payment collection → manufacturing.
- **Military (`Patient::TYPE_MILITARY`)**: skip quote/approval/payment gates; silent background cost; costs roll to sovereign debt reports (`CaseRecord::PATH_MILITARY`).
- **Data isolation**: never mix civilian/military logic in queries, policies, or UI filters without explicit `patient_type` / `path` scoping.

## Tracking technology

- **QR Code**: patient card, quote document, approval scan, delivery close.
- **Barcode**: serialized stock movements — no manual dispense without validated work order + scan match.

## Architecture alignment

- Business logic in **Services** only; controllers return views/JSON.
- Workflow transitions are **event-driven** — no manual "send to department" buttons in backend design.
- UI dashboards: static Blade until backend wired; no fake patient names or demo metrics in JS.

## Key aggregates (existing models)

| Concept | Model / table |
|---------|----------------|
| Patient file | `Patient` |
| Operational case | `CaseRecord` (`cases`) |
| Pricing queue | `PricingRequest` |
| Quote | `Quote` |
| BOM | `Bom` |
| Stock | `StockItem`, `StockMovement` |
| Audit | `AuditLog` (append-only) |
